class MealPlanController extends GetxController {
  final loading = false.obs;
  final showLogin = false.obs;
  var check1 = true.obs;
  var check2 = true.obs;
  var check3 = true.obs;

  late Box momData;

  @override
  void onInit() async {
    super.onInit();
    momData = await Hive.openBox(Constants.MOM_DATA);
    momData.put(0, ["No data available"]);
    momData.put(1, [
      "<p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;' id='isPasted'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Getting Ready and Ovulating</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Pregnancy&#39;s first week is filled with joy to celebrate welcoming your new family member. This week, your body is working hard to create a home for your baby. It is the time of your ovulation.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>When trying to conceive,&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>ovulation</span><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>&nbsp;is the most crucial concept to understand. Pregnancy cannot occur without ovulation. A mature egg will be released from one of your ovaries and will go through your fallopian tube where it&#39;ll be fertilized with your lucky sperm. Egg cells in the fallopian tube wait 24 to 48 hours for sperm. There is a short or limited fertile time.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>A positive pregnancy test around the time of your missing period will tell you if the egg and sperm have successfully fertilized after ovulation.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;text-align: center;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>&quot;Every moment you spend, from preparing for ovulation to learning you are pregnant, brings you one step closer to the wonderful journey of welcoming a new life into the world.&rdquo;</span></p>"
    ]);
    momData.put(2, [
      "<p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;' id='isPasted'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Ovulation &amp; Fertilization</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>The sperm will fertilize your egg before the end of this week. When you ovulate, one of your ovaries releases a mature egg to the fallopian tube. The strongest sperm travels from the uterus to the fallopian tube, where the egg cell waits to meet the sperm.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>If your timing is correct, the fertilization process starts when the winning sperm and egg meet. After fertilization, they travel from the fallopian tube to the uterus. Your uterus will fill with fluid, separating the fertilized egg into two. One will contain the baby, while the other will contain the placenta.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>The genes and gender of your child are decided at the moment of conception. If the egg receives a Y chromosome from the sperm, your child will be a boy; if it receives an X chromosome, it will be a girl.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Most women do not experience any notable changes in the second week. Some may have mittelschmerz, or small cramping on the lower side where the ovary releases an egg, along with a discharge from the vagina that looks like a still-white egg. At two weeks pregnant, your tummy won&#39;t seem to be growing, but you might feel a little more stuffy or gassy than usual.</span></p>"
    ]);

    momData.put(3, [
      "<p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;' id='isPasted'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Implantation and Folic Acid</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Best wishes! You are definitely in the first month of your pregnancy at 3 weeks pregnant.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>After 200 million attempts, the sperm and egg connect and implant. At this moment, the egg turns into a zygote and stops any more sperm from getting in. The zygote also defines whether it will likely be a girl or a boy and gets 200 other genetic characteristics, such as hair and eye color.</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>During this week, getting enough folic acid is important whether you are trying to conceive or are already pregnant.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Folic acid helps prevent neural tube difficulties that occur in a baby&#39;s brain, spinal cord, and heart. Folic acid should be taken as early as three months before fertilization and during the entire pregnancy because these organs start developing in the first few weeks of pregnancy.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Folic acid also promotes the continuous production of red blood cells to avoid anemia. Natural folic acid is available in the following food sources:</span></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>&nbsp;</span></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Brussels sprouts, broccoli, spinach, okra, collard greens, tomato, and asparagus.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Beans, peas, lentils&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Avocado</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Seeds and nuts</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Citrus fruits and juices</span></p></li></ul>"
    ]);

    momData.put(4, [
      "<h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;' id='isPasted'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Early Pregnancy Detection</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>This is the time when the physical changes of pregnancy begin to show. Some physical changes that occur during the early stages of pregnancy include nausea, fatigue, frequent urination, and swollen and sore breasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>But for some women, the only symptom they have is not getting their period. Take a pregnancy test if you missed yours.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>When the fertilized egg crawls into the uterus and produces pressure, it can discharge a few drops of blood, and the placenta and umbilical cord start to grow. It&#39;s not a menstrual cycle, so don&#39;t worry.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>It is best to test after a week because testing on the first day of the menstrual cycle&#39;s end frequently results in false negative results. You should also confirm the same through a blood test at a medical center. You have to be very happy!</span></p><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Advice &amp; Care</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>It&#39;s time to meet and finalize your doctor and to check your medical insurance. (Maternity insurance offers complete coverage for medical expenses incurred during pregnancy, including the cost of delivery, hospitalization, pre- and post-natal care, medical tests, medicines, and newborn baby expenses. With this you will financially prepare for having a baby).</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Dos</span></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Buy a pregnancy test kit for your home.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Eat only home-cooked, healthful meals.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Keep your body at ease and take rests as needed.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Keep in contact with your doctor.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Get folic acid and vitamin B6.</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Vitamins B6</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Pyridoxine, often known as&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>vitamin B6</span><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>, is necessary for pregnant women. This vitamin increases red blood cell synthesis, boosts metabolism, eases morning sickness, and improves brain function.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Vitamin B6 shortage will impact the nervous system, perhaps leading to cramping, fainting, and dizziness.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Vitamin B6 is available in significant amounts in natural sources, such as:</span></p><p><br></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Fish, red meat, eggs</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>strawberries, carrots, avocados</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>nuts, beans, peas</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>cereals</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Spinach</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Other Tips</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>It&#39;s advisable to avoid anything that could cause your body temperature to rise during this week. Fever can harm a baby&#39;s growth because it is unsafe for development.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Still, some women could find sauna bathing benefits to be calming. By raising your body temperature naturally, this therapy promotes sweat production and improves blood circulation. As a result, this reduces pregnancy-related back pain.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>If you really want to have a sauna, do it after the first month. Drink plenty of water before and after using the sauna, and try not to spend more than five minutes there. Lower the heat as much as you can. If you begin to feel uneasy or notice anything strange, leave.</span></p><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Shopping</span></h2><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>This week&#39;s shopping basket stays simple. If you haven&#39;t purchased anything yet, you might want to go with a pregnancy book, a pregnancy test kit, and a cozy cotton bra. With this, you are all set for the first 4 to 5 weeks of pregnancy!</span></p>"
