    momData.put(5, [
      "<h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;' id='isPasted'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Embryo Begins to Form</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>You will begin your second month of pregnancy at 5 weeks. By the fifth week, you will have missed your period by approximately seven days, so you will undoubtedly find out if you are pregnant. The pregnancy symptoms will be stronger around this time. So, take a test for official confirmation.</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Many women experience breast pain, nausea, fatigue, and frequent urination in the first few weeks of pregnancy. Growing a baby is hard work, but your body naturally adjusts to be ready for this!</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>This week, the embryo starts to take shape and develop. The ectoderm is the top layer of the embryo, in which the neural tube also starts to develop. The brain, spinal cord, nerves, and backbone begin to form in the neural tube. Your baby&#39;s arms and legs start to take shape as little buds form. Your baby&#39;s heart begins to beat, and its lungs are growing.</span></p><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>5th Week Ultrasound</span></h2><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>It&#39;s possible that your doctor won&#39;t recommend an ultrasound in week five. A scan may only be recommended to women who have previous experiences of pregnancy problems.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Why Is an Ultrasound Scan at Five Weeks Necessary?</span></p><p><br></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>You should get your first ultrasound scan in the fifth week of your pregnancy, as that&#39;s when the first heartbeat occurs. This will help confirm the baby&#39;s presence inside the womb.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>The fifth-week ultrasound scan will help the doctor check and confirm whether you have one or twin babies.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Your doctor may scan for any abnormalities by ultrasound.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>At this time, an ultrasound can assist verify whether the baby is growing properly. This is especially important if you are expecting twins, this is your second pregnancy, and you have previously experienced a difficult pregnancy.</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Precaution for 5th Week Ultrasound&rsquo;</span></h2><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Before your appointment, drink a lot of water</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Don&#39;t go to the bathroom before the scan.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Prepare yourself in case a transvaginal ultrasound is necessary. (A transvaginal ultrasound can not only confirm pregnancy but also find out diseases such as abnormal growths or pelvic organ disorders. Early identification of these is crucial.)</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>After a trance-vaginal ultrasound, some women report feeling a little painful, although this usually reduces soon.</span></p><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Workouts Tips</span></h2><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Beginning an exercise routine during pregnancy is advisable. Light exercise is enough to increase strength and endurance. Regular exercise can help avoid some pregnancy-related problems, like hip and backaches.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Many women also find exercising useful to reduce stress, especially when tired. However, exercising during pregnancy can help prepare you for the discomforts of delivery.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>What to Eat?</span></h2><p><br></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Look for foods higher in protein than poultry. Nuts, legumes, beans, soy pasta, and some grains are all good choices.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Hate milk? It&#39;s enough to have cheese and yogurt on hand to replace the calcium found in milk.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Include 30% of healthy fats in your pregnancy diet, particularly docosahexaenoic acid (DHA), an omega-3 fatty acid derivative.&nbsp;</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Foods high in omega-3 fatty acids and DHA include:&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Avocados and other fruits are rich in omega-3 fatty acids. It also includes vitamins B6, E, K, and C, potassium, and folate.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#0e101a;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>DHA is also included in several oils, such as canola oil. Cook with this to enhance the consumption of good fats.&nbsp;</span></p></li></ul><p><br></p><h2 dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:6pt;'><span style='font-size:18pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Things to Avoid&nbsp;</span></h2><ul style='margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;'><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Avoid consuming junk food.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Give up drinking, smoking, and taking narcotics.</span></p></li><li dir='ltr' style='list-style-type:disc;font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;'><p dir='ltr' style='line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><span style='font-size:16pt;font-family:Cambria,serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;'>Avoid caffeine.</span></p></li></ul>"
